If an
instance fails, you can launch a replacement Amazon EC2 instance and attach the
Amazon EBS volume to it. This can even be fully automated with the use of Auto Scaling
(to replace the instance) and an initialization script (to attach the Amazon EBS volume to
the new instance).

Keep static contents on S3 & deliver them via cloudfront while dynamic on EC2   . 







